Tokens: smallest unit of a programming language.

Types of tokens:
1.Keywords.
2.Identifiers.
3.Literals.

Keywords: all the characters must be in lower case.

Identifiers:
Rules to write them : 
1.Sholud not atrt with numbers.
2.Spaces are not allowed.
3.Symbols cannot be used (except _ and $ ).
4.Keywords should not be used as Identifier.

Example for :   Class name: Alvas, AlvasCollege.		
		Variable name: alvas, alvasCollege.

Literals: they are known as a value or a data.
	there are 2 types ,
	Primitive and non-Primitive 

Primitive: Numbers , Characters , Booleans.
NOn-Primitive : String literals (any thing which is enclosed with "" is the string data.)

Data types :
 THE TYPE OF DATA WHICH WE TEND TO USE IN THE PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE.

Sizes of datat types:
 byte --1 bytes : 8 bits
 short --2
 int --4
 long --8
 float --4 
 double --8
 character --2 
 boolean --1


Local variables: they can only br used after initialisation.

ASCII Values: A-- 65
	      a-- 95

